<paragraph id="8B94DB56FFD2FFB9FCCCF99AB787998A" blockId="3.[812,1420,1571,1973]" pageId="3" pageNumber="988">
<emphasis id="B95F0744FFD2FFB9FCCCF99AB7879805" box="[813,1420,1571,1595]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="988" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B95F0744FFD2FFB9FCCCF99AB1C09805" bold="true" box="[813,971,1571,1595]" pageId="3" pageNumber="988">Identification.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2BA0D5FFD2FFB9FC3FF99AB6E79805" baseAuthorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[990,1260,1571,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Brachymetra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="988" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albinervus">
<emphasis id="B95F0744FFD2FFB9FC3FF99AB6E79805" box="[990,1260,1571,1595]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="988">Brachymetra albinervus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is extremely
</emphasis>
variable in terms of body size and general coloration, which cannot be reliably used for its recognition. Our specimens were identified based on the following char- acters: antennomere I shorter than II and III together; eye not surpassing the anterolateral angle of the pronotum; pronotum with apex rounded, not reaching the mesoacetabulum, without longitudinal dark brown stripe; fore femur robust and slightly arched, with sparse conical black setae ventrally (
<figureCitation id="1310C7D3FFD2FFB9FBC1F8E1B66F994E" box="[1056,1124,1880,1904]" captionStart="Figures 6, 7" captionStartId="4.[168,239,1301,1321]" captionText="Figures 6, 7. Brachymetra albinervus. 6. Macropterous male, dorsal view.7. Male, fore femur, ventral view." pageId="3" pageNumber="988">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); and dorsum of acetabula with silvery setae. This combination of characters distinguishes them from all known congeners (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBAA6A7FFD2FFB9FB01F825B78A998A" author="Cordeiro IRS" box="[1248,1409,1948,1972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="988" refId="ref15035" refString="Cordeiro IRS (2017) Revisao taxonomica de Brachymetra Mayr, 1865 (Insecta: Heteroptera: Gerridae). Master dissertation, Universidade Federal Rural do Rio de Janeiro, Seropedica, 96 pp." type="book" year="2017">Cordeiro 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
